{"abstract": "We develop the method of stochastic modified equations (SME), in which stochastic gradient algorithms are approximated in the weak sense by continuous-time stochastic differential equations. We exploit the continuous formulation together with optimal control theory to derive novel adaptive hyper-parameter adjustment policies. Our algorithms have competitive performance with the added benefit of being robust to varying models and datasets. This provides a general methodology for the analysis and design of stochastic gradient algorithms.", "referenced_work_ids": ["71683e224ab91617950956b5005ed0439a733a71", "6d4f21e1ef8632de182846958a11d4b16e630180", "2a91c778288f67c856041447f350a1a022fc6554", "1249230a8542cf927cbfa49c30d00f3b8a2f5e43", "206193a222face6428655e3359197c4a4caa291b", "a6cb366736791bcccc5c8639de5a8f9636bf87e8", "d1e4365de165463e51134f10bf3939f2b00a6667", "6a17e23fd63f1bccca7e0e602152ce31170e5945", "f244da7263ef3e5c25a7780c7c2f32ca07a25d12", "c92372db9eec502bfe53c3aed0537a9b4147a6e5", "43c05444fbc239321f6676f3cd539cac34fde7b8", "35c69ff966267a10d72791174e55db8012c410bc", "d9bdff5eac0d0d1ebd8d09960f195b838ce16f4e", "aa7bfd2304201afbb19971ebde87b17e40242e91", "34d5677a71691b09533040a76787d944e72d1f9d", "b4b0a3a748dfd2618ffcf1f94411e339e1e78775", "8729441d734782c3ed532a7d2d9611b438c0a09a", "2672ba89286367fe312f167d85a75b3fbe64b2ab", "522e90b9fccfd3c1c0603359eb04757d770c1ab5", "e5a685f40338f9c2f3e68e142efa217aad16dd56", "c5495df22c2dd9a58bc11fcc8d638c3c502ce32d", "7658cecad68afc970f18cadbf6390439b17def87", "a7e2d53c47bdef073add879557270d915d80a098", "413c1142de9d91804d6d11c67ff3fed59c9fc279", "42008f1580dacfe993ec45eca2105eaec0db330e", "f914646c43eac8f35cc9a480ded031ae9bae1e9e", "e36b12155b8b5e6209e857f79a1821ffe3cddd1f", "f9ba4779af6563ad71c06db968a59a8aca00ef45", "6dc61f37ecc552413606d8c89ffbc46ec98ed887", "a1a2b349d43db56afa1a204c20c9876870f0a694", "a8e8f3c8d4418c8d62e306538c9c1292635e9d27", "88cef2e4761e633bc85790a8ce805fe902c66d3d", "3b80e724e